title: Harry Washington (American football)
data: Harry Washington (born July 30, 1956) is a former American football wide receiver who played for the Minnesota Vikings and the Chicago Bears of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Colorado State University.[1][2][3] Washington was also a noted minor league player.[4][5] This biographical article relating to an American football wide receiver born in the 1950s is a stub.
